Pre-Game Insights: Mitchell Santner, the New Zealand captain, will be aiming to lead his team to victory against the formidable Australian side.
Mitchell Marsh, the Australian captain, will be looking to make an impact as he leads his team in the T20I series against Black Caps.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Sky Stadium, like most venues in New Zealand, features a drop-in pitch that generally favors the batters.
Fast bowlers may find some assistance during the early stages of the match.
Others: The match will take place at the Sky Stadium in Wellington on February 21, 2024, at 11:40 am IST/ 06:10 am GMT / 07:10 pm LOCAL.

The New Zealand squad includes Finn Allen, Devon Conway, Will Young, Rachin Ravindra, Glenn Phillips, Mark Chapman, Mitchell Santner, Ish Sodi, Lockie Ferguson, Adam Milne, Tim Southee, Josh Clarkson, and Ben Sears.

The Australian squad includes David Warner, Travis Head, Mitchell Marsh, Glenn Maxwell, Josh Inglis, Tim David, Pat Cummins, Adam Zampa, Nathan Ellis, Josh Hazlewood, Mitchell Starc, Matthew Short, Steven Smith, and Spencer Johnson.
